<HEADLINE> Michael Jackson in Seoul for Concert </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEOUL, South Korea (AP) -- Michael Jackson arrived in South Korea  
on Monday for a concert to benefit needy children. 
</P>
<P>
	Mariah Carey, Boyz II Men and Elizabeth Taylor will join the pop  
star for the four-hour show on Friday in Seoul. 
</P>
<P>
	It will be Jackson's second concert in Seoul. His 1996  
performance drew tens of thousands of fans. 
</P>
<P>
	Tickets this time are selling for up to $250 a seat, compared  
with up to $66 for local performers. Cheil Communications, the 
promoter, said about 60 percent of the 60,000 seats have been sold. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
