<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Fire Kills Boy, Badly Burns Father </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AMBLER, Pa. (AP) -- A 5-year-old boy playing with matches started  
a fire that killed the little boy and badly burned his father as he 
tried to rescue his four children from their burning row house on 
Father's Day. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire also damaged 14 other row houses.  
</P>
<P>
	The body of Daniel Gaskins was found under debris on the second  
floor of his house after Sunday's fire, which burned out of control 
for three hours in this Philadelphia suburb. 
</P>
<P>
	Daniel started the fire while playing with matches on a sofa  
bed, Whitpain Township police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Daniel's father, 39-year-old Nathan Gaskins, was burned over 20  
percent of his body as he tried to rescue his children. He was in 
critical condition Monday at Crozier-Chester Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
	``I could see him being baked,'' neighbor Estella Clemons said.  
She saw Gaskins lifting one of his twin daughters through a 
second-story window onto their porch roof. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was panicking. The skin was off him,'' said another  
neighbor, Tony Thornton, who grabbed the little girl from Gaskins 
and carried her to safety past flames in his own living room. 
</P>
<P>
	The twin girls were not injured. An 8-year-old brother was in  
good condition with third-degree burns on his arms at St. 
Christopher's Hospital for Children. 
</P>
<P>
	Their mother, Cheryl Gaskins, was home at the time of the fire  
but was uninjured. 
</P>
<P>
	Four firefighters and another person also were injured, fire  
officials said. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
