<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ankiel Selected For Futures Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Pitchers Rick Ankiel of the St. Louis Cardinals  
and Ryan Anderson of the Seattle Mariners were among the players 
selected Monday for the U.S. roster for the first All-Star Futures 
game at Boston's Fenway Park next month. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. team also includes Oakland pitcher Mark Mulder,  
Baltimore pitcher Matt Riley and Houston outfielder Lance Berkman, 
the MVP of last year's Triple-A World Series. Also on the roster is 
Cubs outfielder Corey Patterson, the third pick in the 1998 amateur 
draft. 
</P>
<P>
	Eight Dominicans were selected for the world team, including  
infielders Pablo Ozuna of the Florida Marlins, Aramis Ramirez of 
the Pittsburgh Pirates and Alfonso Soriano of the New York Yankees. 
</P>
<P>
	The world team includes players from Australia, Canada,  
Colombia, Cuba, the Dominican Republic, Jamaica, Japan, Korea, 
Mexico, the Netherlands, Panama, Puerto Rico, Taiwan, the U.S. 
Virgin Islands and Venezuela. 
</P>
<P>
	Twenty-five players were picked for each roster, including at  
least one from each of the 30 major league organizations. 
</P>
<P>
	The game will be played July 11, two days before the All-Star  
game. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
