<HEADLINE> Citizens Buying USTrust for $1.4B </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) -- Citizens Financial Group announced today  
it is purchasing USTrust Corp., which has 87 banking offices in 
eastern Massachusetts, for $1.4 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Citizens is already the second-largest bank in New England, and  
the deal would intensify its presence in eastern Massachussetts. 
</P>
<P>
	The acquisition would increase Citizens' deposits from $15.3  
billion to $19.5 billion and its loan portfolio from $12.5 billion 
to $16.9 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	The move would give Citizens more than 350 branches and nearly  
800 automatic teller machines throughout New England. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
