<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Woman Throws Cash Before Suicide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- A woman plunged to her death from the 29th floor  
of a hotel after throwing jewelry and handfuls of cash out her 
window. 
</P>
<P>
	Police recovered $36,000, all in large denominations, from her  
room and the alley below the St. Moritz Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
	Witnesses said the 56-year-old woman spent about 10 minutes on  
the ledge outside her window Sunday while police and hotel maids 
tried to persuade her to go back inside. 
</P>
<P>
	``She was on the ledge holding on to something, then she leaned  
back, lifted her arms like she surrendered, and she was gone,'' 
Chantal Mytych of West Palm Beach, Fla., told the New York Post. 
</P>
<P>
	Another witness, Carol DeRosa of New Jersey, told the Daily News  
that the woman stretched out her arms ``as if she were doing a 
stunt in a movie.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 689-room hotel is on fashionable Central Park South, but the  
woman's window was on the side facing away from the park. 
</P>
<P>
	Police withheld the woman's identity. She was registered at the  
hotel under an assumed name. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
