<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Stocks End Mixed; Dow Down 39.58  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Blue-chip stocks pulled back today, but  
technology shares rallied for a fifth straight session, pushing the 
Nasdaq market back toward record terrain. The Dow Jones industrial 
average finished 39.58 lower at 10,815.98 after recovering from a 
nearly 100 point slide. The Dow, which rose 365 points last week, 
is about 200 points below the May 3 closing record of 11,014.69. 
Broader stock indicators were mostly positive. The 
technology-dominated Nasdaq composite index rose 2.6 percent, 
finishing about 21 points from its all-time best close of 2,652.05 
set on April 26. It was up 66.84 at 2,630.28. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 
500 index posted a modest gain after turning higher late in the 
day. 

</P>
<P>
	Financial Figures  
</P>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial figures at the close:  
