accepted the resignations of its chief executive and chief 
financial officer less than two months after accounting problems 
forced it to restate earnings. McKesson HBOC is the largest 
pharmaceutical supply management and health care information 
technology company in the United States. McKesson acquired software 
maker HBOC in January. HBOC sells computer software to help health 
care providers manage their businesses. The earnings restatements 
reflected improperly recorded software sales. McKesson shares were 
at 33 3/4, down 2 5/16. 

</P>
