<HEADLINE> Hall of Fame Announcement Delayed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SPRINGFIELD, Mass. (AP) -- A delay during the voting process  
forced the Basketball Hall of Fame to postpone announcing this 
year's inductees Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Kimberley Lee, a hall spokeswoman, said the voting will be  
completed and names announced late this week. The exact date 
remained undecided. 
</P>
<P>
	An inductee must receive 18 of 24 voters on the Honors  
Committee, which includes hall of famers, basketball officials, 
journalists and others. 
</P>
<P>
	The nominees announced earlier this month are Kevin McHale, John  
Thompson, Maurice Cheeks, Gus Johnson, Dennis Johnson, Jo Jo White, 
Robert McAdoo, Sidney Moncrief, Chet Walker, Jim Phelan, Tex 
Winter, Morgan Wootten, Wayne Embry, Grady Lewis, Fred Zollner, 
Drazen Petrovic, Pereira Maciel Ubiratan, Billie Moore and Harley 
Redin. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
