<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Chris Childs Hurts Knee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Backup point guard Chris Childs of the New York  
Knicks sprained his left knee in the first half of Monday night's 
Game 3 of the NBA Finals against San Antonio. 
</P>
<P>
	Childs was hurt when he tried to run down Tim Duncan from  
behind, committed a foul on the play and tumbled to the floor. 
</P>
<P>
	He sat out almost the entire third quarter, returning with just  
over 1 second left in the quarter with his leg heavily wrapped. He 
did, however, start the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
	His injury added to the physical woes of the Knicks, already  
playing without Patrick Ewing, who has a torn Achilles' tendon. 
Larry Johnson sprained his right knee in the final game of the 
Eastern Conference finals against Indiana and Chris Dudley was 
playing with a hyper-extended right elbow. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
