<HEADLINE> Dow Down 37.36; Nasdaq Up 30.50 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices were mixed today as blue-chips fell  
and technology shares rallied to recover a chunk of their recent 
losses. 
</P>
<P>
	At 11 a.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
down 37.36 at 10,818.20 after giving back an early 24-point gain. 
On Friday, the Dow rose about 14 points to finish the week with a 
gain of 365 points. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were mixed today. The Standard &AMP; Poor's  
500 index was down 0.92 at 1,341.92, but the technology-dominated 
Nasdaq composite index was up 30.50 at 2,593.94. 
</P>
<P>
	Technology stocks have been hit hard in recent weeks amid fears  
the Federal Reserve will raise interest rates to slow the economy 
and contain inflation. But with investors now expecting the Fed to 
implement only a small increase, the discounted prices in the 
technology group are looking more attractive. 
</P>
<P>
	IBM was up 2 5/8 at 123 3/8 to cushion the Dow, which was weighed down  
by Chevron, down 2 5/16 at 90 7/8. 
</P>
<P>
	Declining issues barely outnumbered advancers on the New York  
Stock Exchange, where volume came to 209.92 million shares. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was down 1.55 at 635.00, and the  
American Stock Exchange composite index was down 4.25 at 764.42. 

  	   	
</P>
