<HEADLINE> Lewinsky Psychiatrist on Probation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- The license of Monica Lewinsky psychologist  
Irene Kassorla, once described as ``shrink to the stars,'' has been 
placed on probation. 
</P>
<P>
	The state Department of Consumer Affairs on Monday cited  
``repeated negligent acts'' that included failing to keep notes on 
therapy sessions. Kassorla also admitted to referring a patient to 
her husband for a business consultation. 
</P>
<P>
	No further details of the charges were disclosed.  
</P>
<P>
	Kassorla agreed to a settlement that calls for an immediate  
three-year license probation. Kassorla must complete an ethics 
course and repay the state $6,000 in costs. A receptionist said she 
was on vacation in Turkey. 
</P>
<P>
	Kassorla, who counseled Ms. Lewinsky from 1992 through 1997, was  
told by Ms. Lewinsky about her sexual relationship with Clinton. 
She testified that Ms. Lewinsky suffered from depression and low 
self-esteem. 
</P>
<P>
	Kassorla has written several books and makes numerous television  
and radio talk show appearances. 
  	   	
</P>
