<HEADLINE> Stocks Mostly Higher; Dow Up 21.84 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks opened mostly higher today as technology  
shares rallied sharply, outpacing blue-chip stocks. 
</P>
<P>
	At 10 a.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
up 21.84 at 10,877.40. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were mostly higher. The Standard &AMP;  
Poor's 500 index was up 5.57 at 1,348.41, and the Nasdaq composite 
index was up 31.03 at 2,594.47. 
</P>
<P>
	Technology stocks were recovering after being hit hard in recent  
weeks amid fears of an interest rate hike by the Federal Reserve. 
But investors, now expecting the Fed to implement only a small 
increase, were lured today by the tech stocks' more affordable 
prices. IBM, up 3 1/16 at 123 13/16, led the Dow components. 
</P>
<P>
	Brokerage stocks were mostly higher as Wall Street anticipates  
robust earnings reports from several major firms this week. Morgan 
Stanley Dean Witter gained 2 3/8 to 98 1/8. 
</P>
<P>
	On Friday, the Dow Jones Industrial Average rose 13.93 to close  
at 10855.56, ending a week in which the blue chips rose 365 points. 
</P>
<P>
	Advancing issues outnumbered decliners by a 4-to-3 margin today  
on the New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 86.1 million 
shares. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was up 1.60 at 638.15, and the American  
Stock Exchange composite index was down 0.95 at 767.62. 
</P>
<P>
	Overseas, Japan's Nikkei stock average rose 1.76 percent after  
the Bank of Japan bought dollars to hold the yen lower. In 
afternoon trading, Germany's DAX index was up 0.61 percent, 
Britain's FT-SE 100 was down 0.17 percent, and France's CAC-40 was 
up 0.68 percent. 

  	   	
