<HEADLINE> Crate &AMP; Barrel Recalls Kids' Tables </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Home furnishings company Crate &AMP; Barrel is  
recalling about 4,300 children's tables that have six-inch holes in 
the center, because children's heads can become stuck in the holes, 
the Consumer Product Safety Commission said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Crate &AMP; Barrel, of Northbrook, Ill., said it has received four  
reports of children becoming trapped in the table openings, and 
that two children required emergency help to free them. 
</P>
<P>
	The tables in question were sold at the company's stores around  
the country and through a holiday catalog for about $75 alone or 
for $135 as a set with chairs. The tables, 27 inches by 27 inches, 
have a red canvas bag hanging in the hole. 
</P>
<P>
	Crate &AMP; Barrel will provide a free repair part that will  
permanently close the hole. Consumers should call the company at 
800-897-5919 between 9 a.m. and 6 p.m. EDT. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
