<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Kournikova Tries To Focus on Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WIMBLEDON, England (AP) -- No, she's not dating Brazilian soccer  
star Ronaldo. No, she doesn't have a boyfriend. And no, she doesn't 
mind the attention that has made her Wimbledon's cover girl. 
</P>
<P>
	Anna Kournikova dodged a dangerous first-round opponent Monday,  
beating Barbara Schwartz 7-6 (7-2), 4-6, 6-2. Then she shrugged off 
questions about her life off the court. 
</P>
<P>
	``I just concentrate on my tennis,'' she said. ``I'm here to  
play.'' 
</P>
<P>
	But for London tabloids and a swarm of photographers, the tennis  
is incidental. Kournikova, 18, is an international celebrity even 
though she has yet to win a tournament, much less a Grand Slam 
event. 
</P>
<P>
	And so at her postmatch news conference, the main line of  
inquiry was about her boyfriend. When Ronaldo was mentioned, 
Kournikova ruled out any romantic link with a polite smile. 
</P>
<P>
	``The last time I saw him was the only time I saw him, at the  
French Open last year,'' Kournikova said. 
</P>
<P>
	She was seen Sunday at the All England Club with her frequent  
companion, NHL star Sergei Federov, but said: ``I don't have any 
boyfriend.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Has she split up with Federov?  
</P>
<P>
	``No comment to that,'' she said.  
</P>
<P>
	Does she want a boyfriend?  
</P>
<P>
	``I have no comment,'' she said.  
</P>
<P>
	Kournikova would rather talk about tennis, and she looked  
impressive against Schwartz, a hard-hitting left-hander who upset 
Venus Williams at the French Open. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was a tough match,'' Kournikova said. ``I'm happy that I  
went through the first round. That's the most important one.'' 
</P>
<P>
	She is paired for a quarterfinal showdown against seven-time  
champion Steffi Graf. 
</P>
<P>
	Kournikova says grass is her favorite surface, and she reached  
the semifinals in her only previous Wimbledon appearance two years 
ago. She missed last year's tournament with a thumb injury. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
