<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Gov.'s Daughter Cited for Drinking </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JUNEAU, Alaska (AP) -- The governor's daughter and four of her  
friends were cited for underage drinking after they inadvertently 
summoned police to the Governor's Mansion. 
</P>
<P>
	Gov. Tony Knowles and his wife gave permission to their  
19-year-old daughter, Devon, to have eight friends for dinner on 
Friday while they were in Los Angeles, Knowles said in a statement 
Monday. Four planned to spend the night. 
</P>
<P>
	Late in the evening, one of the women picked up a telephone with  
a direct connection to the Juneau Police Department, said Greg 
Wilkinson, a spokesman for the Alaska State Troopers, who provide 
security at the mansion. 
</P>
<P>
	``One of the gals apparently picked up the wrong phone to make a  
phone call,'' Wilkinson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Concerned about possible trouble, police headed for the mansion,  
Wilkinson said. Something must have aroused officers' suspicions 
that the women were drinking alcohol and they conducted breath 
tests, he said. 
</P>
<P>
	If convicted of the violation, the women face a fine of at least  
$100. 
</P>
<P>
	``This incident is being dealt with by the proper authorities  
and by each of the families involved,'' the governor said, refusing 
to comment further. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
