<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Citizens Purchasing USTrust Corp. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- A subsidiary of The Royal Bank Of Scotland  
announced Monday it is acquiring UST Corp. in a deal valued at $1.4 
billion, expanding Citizens' presence in New England. 
</P>
<P>
	Citizens Financial Group will pay $32 for each of UST's  
outstanding shares. 
</P>
<P>
	Boston-based UST is the parent company of USTrust, which has 87  
banking offices in eastern Massachusetts. 
</P>
<P>
	The deal comes amid major shifts in the New England banking  
industry. 
</P>
<P>
	In March, the Fleet Financial Group Inc. announced it was  
merging with BankBoston. Fleet is the largest bank in New England, 
and BankBoston is the second-largest. 
</P>
<P>
	After that merger, Citizens would rank as the region's  
second-largest bank. And it will expand with the purchase of UST. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're going to be the pre-eminent bank of choice in this part  
of New England,'' said Lawrence K. Fish, chairman, president and 
CEO of Citizens. 
</P>
<P>
	The acquisition of UST would increase Citizens' deposits from  
$15.3 billion to $19.5 billion and its loan portfolio from $12.5 
billion to $16.9 billion. 
</P>
<P>
	Citizens will have more than 350 branches throughout New England  
and nearly 800 automated teller machines, the financial group said. 
That will make it the 33rd largest bank in the United States, it 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The purchase will bring new lines of business to Citizens,  
including investment management and insurance brokerage. 
</P>
<P>
	The two institutions have identified a combined 800 positions  
that would be made obsolete by the acquisition. 
</P>
<P>
	Fish said the companies also have a combined 500 open positions,  
and efforts will be made to absorb employees into those spots 
rather than lay them off. 
</P>
<P>
	UST currently has about 2,000 employees; Citizens has more than  
5,800. 
</P>
<P>
	Citizens last month announced plans to buy the commercial and  
retail business of another Boston-based bank, State Street Corp., 
for $350 million. 
</P>
<P>
	Bank officials in Providence, R.I., where Citizens is  
headquartered, said that Neal F. Finnegan, UST's president and CEO, 
will become non-executive chairman of Citizens Bank of 
Massachusetts and a director of Citizens Financial Group. 
</P>
<P>
	Citizens Financial Group operates Citizens Bank in Connecticut,  
Massachusetts, New Hampshire and Rhode Island. 
</P>
<P>
	UST generated a pretax profit of $90 million in fiscal 1998.  
</P>
<P>
	Pending regulatory approval, the companies hope to close the  
deal by January. 


  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
