<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Man Sentenced for Biting Wife's Lip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- A man was sentenced to five years probation Monday  
for biting off his wife's lower lip during an argument over a party 
he wanted to attend. 
</P>
<P>
	Cator Lewis-Charles, 36, of Boston, pleaded guilty in Superior  
Court to mayhem. He must complete an anger management course and a 
batterer's program. 
</P>
<P>
	The argument on Jan. 2, 1998, at the couple's home escalated  
into pushing and shoving. Lewis-Charles grabbed his wife and bit 
her lower lip, tearing it from her face, said prosecutors, who 
didn't disclose the wife's name. 
</P>
<P>
	Lewis-Charles called 911 and his wife's lip was retrieved and  
re-attached. 
</P>
<P>
	The couple continues to live together with their two sons.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
