<HEADLINE> Stocks Mixed; Dow Down 81.37 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mixed today, with technology shares  
rallying for a fourth straight session and blue-chip shares giving 
back some of last week's gains. 
</P>
<P>
	At 2 p.m. on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
down 81.37 at 10,774.19 after surrendering an early 24-point gain. 
The Dow rose 365 points last week, gaining 14 points on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Broader stock indicators were mixed today. The Standard &AMP; Poor's  
500 index was down 1.75 at 1,341.09, but the technology-dominated 
Nasdaq composite index was up 37.59 at 2,601.03. 
</P>
<P>
	Technology stocks have been hit hard in recent weeks amid fears  
the Federal Reserve will raise interest rates to slow the economy 
and contain inflation. But with investors now expecting the Fed to 
implement only a small increase, the discounted prices in the 
technology group are looking more attractive. 
</P>
<P>
	Among leading Nasdaq technology issues, Dell Computer was up 1  
47/64 at 38 7/16, Microsoft was up 1 53/64 at 86 53/64 and Intel 
was up 1 5/8 at 56 9/16. 
</P>
<P>
	IBM was up 3 at 123 3/4 to cushion the Dow, which was being weighed  
down by Alcoa, off 4 5/8 at 62 15/16, and Chevron, off 2 9/16 at 90 5/8. 
</P>
<P>
	Declining issues outnumbered advancers by a small margin on the  
New York Stock Exchange, where volume totaled a sluggish 440.64 
million shares, while advancers held a narrow lead in Nasdaq 
trading. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was down 2.52 at 634.03, while the  
American Stock Exchange composite was down 4.95 at 763.62. 

  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
